{{about-otherpeople|a priest and philosopher from Laodicea|Proculeius|Proculeia gens}} '''Proclus''' ({{lang-el|Πρόκλος}}) or '''Proculeius''', son of the physician [[Themison (physician)|Themison]]. Was [[hierophant]] at [[Latakia|Laodiceia]] in [[Syria]]. He wrote, according to the [[Suda]], the following works:
*''On the gods'' (θεολογία) *''On the myth of Pandora in Hesiod'' (εἰς τὴν παρ' Ἡσιόδῳ τῆς Πανδώρας μῦθον) *''On golden words'' (εἰς τὰ χρυσᾶ ἔπη) *''On Nicomachus' introduction to number theory'' (εἰς τὴν Νικομάχου εἰσαγωγὴν τῆς ἀριθμητικῆς) *some geometrical treatises
